main event: Four objects were observed stationary overhead in Taiwan for about 4.5 minutes. At various intervals, three other objects were observed for 4 minutes, 10 minutes, and 1 minute.
interesting points: The objects were too close to the sun for identification as the sunlight reflected off them, and they were too small to be identified as aircraft or balloons.
The flight characteristics of the objects, including starting, stopping, and making right angle turns, did not match known aircraft or balloon behavior.
Other similar sightings were reported in the area.
The sightings lasted for varying lengths of time, from 1 minute to over 10 minutes.
No photographs or physical evidence of the objects were obtained.
sighted object: Four stationary objects, plus three additional objects observed at different times
